what the chance what is the chance of getting pregnant while taking zovia and not using a condom zovia inhibits ovulation via a negative feedback mechanism of the hypothalamus it also changes the cervical mucus rendering it unfavorable for sperm penetration even if ovulation occurs therefore the chances of becoming pregnant while taking any bcp is minimal if taken at the same time every day do remember that being unwell can alter the effectiveness of the bcp so using further protection if this happens is advisable hope this helps Fertility awareness Menstrual cycle Ovulation Birth control Oral contraceptive Puberty Pregnancy Enzyme In vitro fertilisation Estradiol Signal transduction Seed Oral sex Progesterone Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Infertility Fertilisation Human papillomavirus Cancer Health issues and the effects of cannabis Feedback Safe sex Homeostasis Androgen insensitivity syndrome Electroconvulsive therapy Stomach cancer Human chorionic gonadotropin Psoriasis Blackjack Herpes simplex virus Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Prostate cancer Ovary Pregnancy test Folic acid Gonadotropin-releasing hormone Chemotherapy Cervical cancer Flowering plant Glucokinase Miscarriage Negative feedback Fever Gonorrhoea Sleep Sexual abstinence Stopping power HIV Greenhouse effect Stuttering Nutrition Pornographic movie Corrosion Hypnosis Polycystic ovary syndrome Methotrexate Appetite Amiodarone Schizophrenia Ovarian cyst Sexual reproduction Warfarin Dither Abortion Mobile phone radiation and health Cystic fibrosis Synaptic plasticity Chlorpromazine Estrus cycle Tank Antiretroviral drug Climate change Cervical cap Common cold Condom Second language acquisition Abortion debate Immune system Hypothalamic-pituitary-adrenal axis Female reproductive system (human) Sexually-transmitted infection Carcinogenesis Obesity Cosmic Era technology Cannabis (drug) AIDS Business continuity planning Breastfeeding Oxytocin Premature birth Malaria Slippery slope Aromatase inhibitor Paracetamol